Note: OOP Test

Define a class called Person with properties name, age.

Define a method called greet for Person that takes no parameters and does the following.
    Say "Hello, my name is" plus name.
    Say "I am" plus age plus "years old".
End method.

Define a method called celebrateBirthday for Person that takes no parameters and does the following.
    Let age be age plus 1.
    Say "YAY! Happy Birthday" plus name plus "! Now I am" plus age.
End method.

Say "--- Creating Alice ---".
Let alice be a new Person with name: "Alice", age: 30.

Say "--- Calling greet on Alice ---".
Call greet on alice.

Say "--- Calling celebrateBirthday on Alice ---".
Call celebrateBirthday on alice.

Say "--- Verifying property access ---".
Say "Final age:".
Say the age of alice.

Say "--- Updating property directly ---".
Set the age of alice to 50.
Say "Updated age:".
Say the age of alice.
